# Manantial API

## Prerequisites

Set the following environment variables:

```bash
export MANANTIAL_API_TOKEN="your_api_key_here"
```

Generate your API key from the [/profile](<%= base_url %>/profile) page in the Manantial web application.

## Available Scripts

- **`scripts/manantial-api.sh`** — CLI tool for interacting with the Manantial API

## Setup

1. Download the script to your skill's `scripts/` directory:

```bash
curl -o scripts/manantial-api.sh "<%= base_url %>/api/skills/manantial-api.sh" && chmod +x scripts/manantial-api.sh
```

2. Set your API token:

```bash
export MANANTIAL_API_TOKEN="your_api_key_here"
```

Generate your API key from the [/profile](<%= base_url %>/profile) page.

## Usage

Run the script using relative paths from the skill directory root:

```bash
# List all posts
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh posts

# Get a specific post by slug
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh post my-post-slug

# Create a new post
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh create '{"title": "My New Post", "body": "Post content here"}'

# Update an existing post
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh update my-post-slug '{"title": "Updated Title"}'

# Delete a post
bash scripts/manantial-api.sh delete my-post-slug
```

Run `bash scripts/manantial-api.sh --help` for full usage information.
